  url          = {https://doi.org/10.1038/s41514-025-00293-2},
  keywords     = {ANS, sympathetic, parasympathetic, aging hallmarks, mitochondria, inflammaging, senescence, vagus nerve, alpha7-nAChR, PGC-1alpha, AMPK, NF-kB, gut dysbiosis},
  certainty    = {0.45},
  research_stream = {ans-aging},
  note         = {Perspective article (no original data). Proposes chronic SNS dominance as unifying driver of all 9 hallmarks of aging. Mechanisms: catecholamines/NADPH oxidase→ROS→mtDNA damage; PKA/cAMP→AMPK inhibition→blocked autophagy; beta-AR desensitization→NF-kB inflammaging; cortisol→gut permeability/dysbiosis. PNS protection via alpha7-nAChR→NF-kB inhibition/JAK2-STAT3; PGC-1alpha→mitochondrial biogenesis. Theoretical framework needing empirical validation in ME/CFS. Published npj Aging (Nature Portfolio). ME/CFS relevance: ANS imbalance is core ME/CFS feature; framework integrates multiple ME/CFS pathophysiology threads.}
}

